Recent Press



DAILY MAIL UK
A young Queensland girl diagnosed with leukaemia has delivered the match ball to her State of Origin heroes...
Piper, 14, is undergoing treatment...following her diagnosis friends have set up a GoFundMe page to help pay for Piper's medical costs.
"With the shock diagnosis last week of Piper's Acute Leukaemia, myself as a friend just wanted to know how I could help", her friend shared.


July 13, 2017


THE ATLANTIC
"More than 8,500 GoFundMe campaigns created to raise money for fertility treatments have collected $13 million in the last six years."
July 12, 2017


PARADE
When Todd Arredondo, 32, saw a post making the rounds on social media of a family in his community who created a makeshift swimming pool by lining their pickup truck with a tarp and filling it with water... tracked down the family and gave them an inflatable pool....created a GoFundMe online page to solicit donations, and has raised more than $20,000 from supporters all over the world. Last summer, he gave away pools to 122 underprivileged families and founded Pools for Kids, a nonprofit organization dedicated to providing safe summer fun for children.


July 11, 2017




